  {
    "title": "Property Tax/Rent Rebate",
    "url": "https://pasenatorsaval.com/tth/property-tax-rent-rebate/",
    "date": null,
    "raw_text": "Property Tax/Rent Rebate\nProperty Tax/Rent Rebate\nMarch 6, 2025\nhttps://pasenatorsaval.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/TTH-PTRR-March-2024.mp3\nOn Thursday, March 6, Senator Saval hosted a telephone town hall on\nupdates to the\nProperty Tax/Rent Rebate Program\n. Our district has one of the highest costs of living in Pennsylvania, and many of our neighbors are cost-burdened by rent or property taxes, making this program crucial to offset some of these high expenses.\nThe Property Tax/Rent Rebate Program supports homeowners and renters across Pennsylvania. This program provides a rebate ranging from $380 to $1,000 to eligible older adults and people with disabilities age 18 and older.\nIncome\nMaximum Rebate\n$0 – $8,270\n$1,000\n$8,271 – $15,510\n$770\n$15,511 – $18,610\n$460\n$18,611 – $4 6,520\n$380\nPennsylvania homeowners and renters are eligible for this program if they are ages 65 and older, are widowed and ages 50 and older, or are living with disabilities and ages 18 and older—and meet the above income requirements.\nSupplemental Rebates\nSupplemental rebates provide an additional $190 to $500 in relief to applicants with the most need. These rebates are automatically calculated for property owners with $31,010 or less in income whose property taxes are more than 15% of their total income, and for those who live in these locations:\nPhiladelphia\nScranton\nPittsburgh\nIncome\nStandard\nRebate\nSupplement\n(Kicker)\nTotal Max\nRebate\n$0 – $8,270\n$1,000\n$500\n$1,500\n$8,271 – $15,510\n$770\n$385\n$1,155\n$15,511 – $18,610\n$460\n$230\n$690\n$18,611 – $31,010\n$380\n$190\n$570\nRebates will be distributed beginning July 1, as required by law. First-time filers should anticipate that it will take additional time to review their applications and process their rebates.\nLearn more about the Property Tax/Rent Rebate Program from the\nDepartment of Revenue’s website\nor by calling 1-888-222-9190.\nFor personalized help or to request a paper application booklet, contact Senator Saval’s office: (267) 668-3550 or\nsaval@pasenate.com\n.\nTo join our\nnext\nconversation, please complete the form below and we will call you before the event starts. You can also come back here to listen in online. Please note that you must sign up by noon on the day of the event to be included.\nNewsroom\n→ Press Releases\n→ Video\n→ Audio\n→ Newsletters\n→ Media Mentions\n→ Media Requests\n→ Photo Gallery\n→ Upcoming Events",
    "ai_summary": {
      "summary": "Senator Saval hosted a telephone town hall on March 6, 2025 to inform constituents about the existing Property Tax/Rent Rebate Program, a state program that provides annual rebates of $380 to $1,500 to eligible older adults, widowed individuals, and people with disabilities based on income. The release provides details about eligibility requirements and rebate amounts but describes no new legislation or policy action taken by the senator. The senator's office is offering assistance to constituents who want help applying.",
      "action_type": "event",
      "topics": [
