istrict 16\nMemo:\nEmpowering Municipalities to Place a Moratorium on Data Center Development\n- opens in a new tab\nShort Title:\nAn Act amending the act of July 31, 1968 (P.L.805, No.247), known as the Pennsylvania Municipalities Planning Code, in zoning, providing for optional moratorium on filing or consideration of new applications for high impact data centers.\nLast Action:\nPN 1766\nRe-referred to\nRULES AND EXECUTIVE NOMINATIONS\n,  June 30, 2026\nHB 2426\nRep. Anthony Bellmon\nD\nHouse District 203\nMemo:\nRiver Pilots – Changing the Maximum Draft Size from Twenty-Seven Feet to Twenty-Nine Feet\n- opens in a new tab\nShort Title:\nAn Act amending the act of March 29, 1803 (P.L.542, No.156), entitled \"An act to establish a Board of Wardens for the port of Philadelphia, and for the regulation of pilots and pilotages, and for other purposes therein mentioned,\" further providing for pilots in the Delaware Bay and River.\nLast Action:\nPN 3281\nRe-referred to\nAPPROPRIATIONS\n,  June 30, 2026\nLooking for\nSession laws\nenacted by the\nPennsylvania General Assembly\n?\nPlease reference our Statutes page which contains information on Consolidated, Unconsolidated, and the Constitution of Pennsylvania\nCLICK HERE FOR MORE INFORMATION",
